entries.femaleVariant: [Sit] Tough customer, that Vasquez.
Got a tough customer with that Vasquez – even for a badge.
Props – really well played, that.
What do you make of it all?
Guy just might be the biggest nutjob I've ever seen, but it's still corporate exploitation.
If he's as crazy as you say, why's he so important to you?
entries.maleVariant: If he's as crazy as you say, why is he so important to you?

entries.femaleVariant: Fine.
Fine. Deal.
No way.
My answer's no.
Very wise choice.
Why do I think you don't understand what I'm offering you… ?
Understand just fine. Let's go inside.
Fucking pathetic.
I'm sorry it had to end this way.
Fuck off.
Just go already!
Pay me more and I will.
Please, I know the kinds of budgets BDs get. You can do better than that. Lots better.
entries.maleVariant: Please, I know what kind of budgets BDs get. You can do better than that. Lots better.

entries.femaleVariant: Fine! Triple... and you disappear like the morning dew off North Oak front yards.
Don't follow me in. I'll tell Stephenson you said goodbye.
Not bad, for a petty merc off the streets…
What's going on here?
Corpocunts like that annoy the fuck out of me.
Grown curious how this'll all end.
In pain and profit, that's how. One's sacred, the other's insane, though who knows if they aren't congruous concepts.
Corporats... think they can solve everything with eddies...
And you proved her wrong. Just don't make her desperate, she's liable to bite back.
Joshua deserves our support.
Joshua deserves better company than us.
C'mon, two sinners is just what Jesus of Arroyo needs.
Deal.
[Get out] Joshua needs psychiatric care.
Honestly? Can't rightly make up my mind about him.
entries.maleVariant: Honestly? Can't rightly make my mind up about him.

entries.femaleVariant: So, what do you think about our next, big BD star?
[Get out] He's a true believer.
[Get out] Seems like a nice guy.
[Get out] Can't make up my mind about him.
He's a true believer if I've ever seen one.
entries.maleVariant: He's a true believer if I ever saw one.

entries.femaleVariant: He's got some organic chips loose, needs psychiatric help.
Nah, he seems nice... y'know, for a murderer.
entries.maleVariant: Seems nice... y'know, for a murderer.

entries.femaleVariant: Hmm... my thoughts exactly. But it's too late for that.
He's a true nutcase, that's what he is. But that's beside the point.
Nice? Maybe. But I'd go with completely lost and unhinged.
Some people are only nice because they're afraid of getting hurt. Or 'cause their religion tells 'em to be.
Lemme help you out.
Stephenson's a very disturbed man whose obsession with guilt is driving him to the brink of insanity.
Because Stephenson's got a little somethin' that's in short supply but in very high demand.
That little somethin's called authenticity. In that brain composed entirely of cat shit at this point, he truly believes what he says.
Ah, the perfect actor.
Ah, sounds like the perfect BD actor.
entries.maleVariant: Huh, sounds like the perfect BD actor.

entries.femaleVariant: Think he might be more self-possessed than you think.
Think you might be underestimating him.
Mhm, and one incapable of fucking up in any way.
Look, you're no shrink and neither am I. We're both just out to get paid.
Stephenson could be a fat, old, fucking gold vein for our studio…
And that's my concern because...?
You're fucking with his mind, asking probing questions. You're making him doubt, and most importantly, jeopardizing my investment.
So I'm prepared to pay you double what he's promised you to quietly walk away.
Very wise choice.
Don't follow me in. I'll tell Stephenson you said goodbye.
Fucking pathetic.
But yeah, I'm curious, too. And I've been surprised before.
A thief and a terrorist. I'm in!
Vasquez – he blue inside and out?
Really wonder what kind of dirt you're holdin' on Vasquez.
Can we please talk about something besides faith?
Chatter's pointless – that's enough. Stephenson can't be distracted, he has to focus now.
Fuck off already.
What do you do to relax, Rachel?
Tell me about this braindance.
This braindance – I'm curious, tell me more.
Title's "The Passion" – we're speakin' to the LCD, of course. And it's gonna revolutionize BD.
How so?
Well, Stephenson's furlough is only so long. We can only scroll the last bit with him.
But we'll fill in the run-up to the finale with BD doubles and emobank assets. It'll feel like Stephenson, though.
How is that even possible?
entries.maleVariant: How's that even possible?

entries.femaleVariant: Gimme a break, we're part of EBM. Infinite investment in tech. Couple of years and we won't be using actors anymore. I dream of the day…
So why Josh? Sounds like you don't even need him now.
The Son of Man's agony – you can't weave it strictly out of digital threads just yet.
What's your part in all this?
Can we please stop talking about faith?
And you? Get any say in all this?
He forced the writers to go with the Christian Gospel according to Luke. They'd originally opted for John.
Mm. Guess that's important for…
entries.maleVariant: Guess that's, uh... important for…

entries.femaleVariant: John's version is crude and over the top – the Gospel of Luke speaks more to my sensibility.
Besides, Luke's Christ is prepared for what awaits him. I want the world to understand that – feel it.
Sound like an actor who wants to really become the role.
So what're you trying to convey to the world?
Sound like an actor who really wants to become the part.
entries.maleVariant: Y'sound like an actor who really wants to become the part.

entries.femaleVariant: So what is it you want to convey, exactly?
That Christ was merciful and continues to die for the world's sins.
I only have one shot at this, I... I need to make it count.
Joshua and I are talking, so fuck off, will ya?
entries.maleVariant: Joshua and I are talkin' – so fuck off, will ya?

entries.femaleVariant: Might as well've been born with a badge.
Must have some solid dirt on him, then.
The studio's majority stakeholder's a corp. Unlike you, Vasquez would clearly mind having enemies in high places.
Josh, your night. Topic of choice?
Uhh... I-I dunno, heh, I-I spent years not talking to anyone…
OK. Nothing hard. What do you do to relax?
entries.maleVariant: OK. Nothin' hard. What do you do to relax?

entries.femaleVariant: Uhhh, haha, well let's see I... I-I read scripture, watch braindances and movies. Did you hear about the remake of "Badlands Raid"?
Remake kicks the original's ass.
Nothing like an original.
Never saw either.
Never saw either – braindances aren't my thing.
Original's always the original. And ten times better.
entries.maleVariant: The original's always the original. And ten times better.

entries.femaleVariant: Yeah, kicks the original's ass, trust me.
Relax, Rachel.
Yes, why, I don't know anything about you. How do you spend your leisure time? What do you do to unwind?
None of your fuckin' business.
I mean it as a serious question.
I meditate.
Excuse me?! Realize the stakes here. Tomorrow, this guy's gonna create his masterwork.
He needs to focus, keep his head in the game and put in the performance of his lifetime. There aren't any do-overs.
I'd... like to rest, now…
Perfect timing. Your job's done here – you can go. And don't worry, you'll get your fuckin' money.
Goodbye, V.
Didn't take you for one with a spiritual side.
Glad it works for you.
Didn't take you for one with a spiritual side, you being, well, heh... you.
entries.maleVariant: Didn't take you for one with a spiritual side, you being, heh, well... you.

entries.femaleVariant: Great to have an outlet, something to give you peace of mind.
Know what your problem is, all of you?
True peace of mind can only come through the spirit of divine grace.
You refuse to understand that spirituality can only ever be personal.
That's cynical.
Just plain feel bad for him.
Your cynicism's startin' to wear thin on me.
entries.maleVariant: Your cynicism is startin' to wear thin on me.

entries.femaleVariant: I just feel bad for him.
Doesn't matter, long as it's made him a better man.
Doesn't matter, long as he's a better man than he used to be…
entries.maleVariant: It doesn't matter, as long as he's a better man than he used to be…

entries.femaleVariant: We could talk in circles, but who cares what we think. What would it change? Corps'll continue grow rich off his type, and the masses'll live on with their pipe dreams.
He's fucked in the head, the world's fucked in the head – and you're fucked in the head 'cause MY fucked up head is inside it.
Guess if you want to save the world, that's the first step – get fucked in the head.
Wait up a sec. I wanna talk.
Don't do it, V.
And why the fuck are you here, anyway? For the free meal?
Tell you why I'm here.
Tell you exactly why. I--
Back off me, OK?
Back off.
No! I don't give the slimmest shit what you have to say!
And maybe you should fuck off, huh? You're not part of our group!
Ugh! All this talk about grace and salvation and transformation! I could puke.
Take it from a BD producer, religion's an elaborate lie. All of 'em.
But, heh, Rachel...
No, we're done for the day. Finish your meal, we'll put you up at the studio.
And you? Get lost. You'll get your fee soon.
Goodbye, V. I am truly glad to have met you.
Really believe you're like Jesus?
entries.maleVariant: You really believe you're like Jesus?

entries.femaleVariant: I... I believe we should all follow his example.
Joshua?
entries.maleVariant: Josh?

entries.femaleVariant: Don't even feel sorry for him.
Don't even feel sorry for him... in the least.
Whaddaya think? God exist?
entries.maleVariant: What do you think? God exist?

entries.femaleVariant: You think God exists?
Agh, weird as fuck, today. Heh, just kinda... unreal. But reality beckons.
entries.maleVariant: Weird as fuck, today. Just… kinda unreal. But reality beckons.

entries.femaleVariant: Let's get outta here.
Hang on, where's rebel Johnny? Seem to have lost him.
Well, I found him. He's inside that guy. He's the real rebel.
Make up your mind. Which is it – nutjob or messiah?
C'mon. We got places to trash.
Fuck. Kill me, please.
C'mon, serious question.
What, why? So you flatlined, then got your beat back. Don't tell me that's left you wondering if a construct can even be saved.
All right. Let's go.
Gonna tell me you don't think about being a digital psyche? Possible consequences thereof? Really?
Construct's not a soul. Different things.
I died and rose again. Can't deny that.
Truth is I died and rose again. Plain and simple.
Uh-huh. So, what was that? A miracle? What's it make you – a messiah, a phoenix or a factory-restored, early model Archer?
I got no fuckin' idea what it was and neither do you.
entries.maleVariant: Got no fuckin' idea what it was and neither do you.

entries.femaleVariant: Tell you exactly what brought you back – a clever bit of corpo tech. If there's a true messiah among us, I'll tell you who it is – Saburo Arasaka.
Mhm, one you'd summarily execute if you ran into him.
entries.maleVariant: Hah, one you'd summarily execute if you ran into him.

entries.femaleVariant: See, that's why I'm me and you're you. You drop to your knees before gods. I drop them, pop 'em right between the eyes.
I mean, are you already dead? Or alive till the last existing digighost of you is shredded?
Meanin', like am I gonna ascend to digiheaven?
Descent to digi-hell's more likely, but... yeah. If there is life after death, is Silverhand already livin' the afterlife? Meanin' I'm talkin' to his animated epitaph?
entries.maleVariant: Descent to digi-hell's more likely, but yeah. If there is life after death, is Silverhand already livin' the afterlife? Meanin' I'm talkin' to his animated epitaph?

entries.femaleVariant: I don't give it an ounce of thought – surprise. To me I'm just that... me. No netherworld, no happy wonderworld, just duped, digital psyches.
Seen every kind of dirtbag in this city. This Jesus shit ain't foolin' me.
You even think about makin' a break for it, your ass is goin' down.
Nobody's paying you to open your mouth, Vasquez.
He is set in his ways, like so many men.
[Stand]
[Stand]
Can we change the subject?
